xr: Use the new facilities to deal with the sRGB texture problem

For Vulkan and D3D12, we use the new viewFormat argument, where we
pass in the stripped (non-SRGB) format, while reporting the true
texture format (typically, with OpenXR, SRGB) as format.

What we want to get is:
- XR provides a rgba8-srgb texture
- pass it on without lying, but specify rgba8 as our "view" format
- on the QRhi side this means creating VkImageView (or the equivalents)
  with the view format when rendering into the texture and also when
  setting up the multisample resolve. (instead of just using the
  texture's VkFormat)

Until now this was not strictly required and we could just lie about
the format so that the VkImageViews (or equivalents) used our
fake (non-SRGB) format. This does not with with MSAA and Vulkan
(with some implementations at least), so stop lying, which causes
Qt Quick to create an SRGB texture for the intermediate multisample
color buffer as well. (and so rendering is rgba8-srgb viewed as
rgba8 in both the non-MSAA and MSAA case, while resolve is also
rgba8-srgb viewed as rgba8)

D3D11 does not support this since creating an RTV with a different type
would only be possible if the texture was created with a _TYPELESS
format (not _UNORM, not _SRGB, etc.). So instead, we continue to pass in
the non-sRGB format (e.g. RGBA8_UNORM) in place of the _SRGB one so that
QRhiTexture and everything else in QRhi thinks that it's UNORM, not
SRGB, and that's what the RTV is created with as well. This still
seems to work (not clear why), and avoids the unwanted sRGB conversions.

Use the new, unified fromXxxxTexture() overload in QQuickRenderTarget.
The previous approach with different fromXxxxTextureMultiView etc. is
dropped in favor of a single function that takes viewFormat, arraySize,
and flags.

Make correct use of the uvPosition property when picking Items

When picking 2D items embedded in the scene, the pickResult.uvPosition
property will contain the position value in the picked items coordinate
space. It makes sense to reuse the property for this because (we do it
already internally), and embedded items don't have a texture that
requires a UV, but the idea is the same.

This change makes sure that pickResult has the correct value mapped, and
this is now documented in pickResult.

Fix single pick methods when picking in scenes with 2d items

All of the pick methods that were expected to only return a single pick
result could be wrong when used in a scene with embedded 2d items. This
would happen when the nearest intersecting item was the plane of an
embedded 2d item. We would only return a single item to the frontend
that could be invalid (the hit was on the plane of a 2d item, but not
within its bounds). So it is important that all of our internal picking
methods always return a possible list of intersections for the case that
there are embedded 2d items.

This change makes it where the backend returns lists of possible hits,
and the frontend will return the best option.

Change-Id: I1907cfe0da9fbe972bf4f8dbe416c3fba40e3d89
Reviewed-by: Jonas Karlsson <jonas.karlsson@qt.io>

Allow Item2D (Embedded 2D Quick) to report pick results

Previously we went through the effort to calculate a pick result for all
Item2Ds in the scene, specifically for handling automatic input support.
But it's possible that with generic raycasting that a user would want to
know if the ray intersected with an Item2D, and specifically which one.
This change adds support for doing that.

Also because this change adds an enum to the pick result class, it needs
to be exposed properly to QML as a named value type (since it's a
Q_GADGET). But that also means correcting all the incorrect
documentation.

PickResult is actually "pickResult" since this is a value type and must
start with a lower-case letter.
